# HealthBridge Backend
This is the backend of the HealthBridge application, a healthcare platform designed to manage users, appointments, and yoga classes through RESTful APIs.

## Overview
The backend is built using Node.js and Express.js and follows the MVC (Model-View-Controller) architecture. It provides APIs for user authentication, appointment booking, and yoga class management. MongoDB is used as the database.

## Tech Stack
- Node.js
- Express.js
- MongoDB
- Mongoose
- JSON Web Token (JWT)
- bcryptjs
- dotenv
- CORS

## Architecture
The project follows MVC architecture:
- Models → Define database schema (User, Appointment, YogaClass)
- Controllers → Handle business logic (auth, booking, classes)
- Routes → Define API endpoints
- Middleware → Handle authentication and request validation

## Features
- User registration and login (JWT based authentication)
- Secure password hashing using bcrypt
- Appointment booking system
- Yoga class management
- Protected routes using middleware
- RESTful API design

## API Flow
1. Client sends request to API
2. Route handles the request
3. Controller processes logic
4. Database interaction using Mongoose
5. Response returned to client

## Authentication
- Passwords are hashed using bcrypt before storing
- JWT tokens are generated during login
- Protected routes require token verification

## Project Structure
- controllers/ → Business logic
- models/ → Database schemas
- routes/ → API endpoints
- middlewares/ → Authentication logic
- index.js → Entry point of server

## Run Locally
```bash
npm install
npm start
